    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Will Smith** and **Lawrence Butler** anchor our offense with elite efficiency scores of 74.95 and 73.47, respectively. **Will Smith** benefits from a high-run-environment matchup against Tomoyuki Sugano, where the combination of the #3 spot and a favorable park factor significantly elevates his floor. Similarly, **Lawrence Butler** is a priority start; despite a lower lineup position, his dynamic platoon advantage against Davis Martin and strong park factors make him a high-upside play for our power-starved categories. We also remain bullish on **Tyler Freeman**, whose 65.54 score is bolstered by the stolen base potential against the slow delivery of Tyler Glasnow\u2014a critical factor given our strategic emphasis on speed.\n\nThe rotation selection was tight, with **Jeremiah Jackson** proving to be the most difficult cut. His score of 52.04 was respectable, but he ultimately ceded the utility spot to **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, whose higher base projection and reliable #3 order slot provided a safer path to production against Chris Bassitt. **Cal Raleigh** warrants a secondary watch; his score of 46.92 sits near our marginal threshold, primarily due to the daunting matchup against Jacob deGrom. While his power upside is ever-present, the negative park factor and elite pitching skill of deGrom make him the most volatile piece of today's lineup. \n\nRisk management remains a primary focus, as we are navigating a high volume of \"Lineup Pending\" designations for **Luis Arraez**, **Gleyber Torres**, and **Daulton Varsho**. Should any of these players drop lower than their assumed order spots, their daily efficiency scores will fluctuate downward, potentially impacting our aggregate projection. We are comfortable with our current configuration, but we will monitor for any late-breaking weather reports or defensive changes that could force a pivot to bench options like **Gavin Sheets** or **Wenceel Perez**, should a higher-ceiling opportunity arise.",
